<br>
Not that I'd mind if we were unbalanced <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
My thought is that Innate Wiz crits should stack with AA crits...<br>
<br>
Meaning 1 in 50 AA crits would <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>also</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> happen to be an innate crit... <br>
<br>
I am not a statistician, but that would mean one in 500 or so nukes would &quot;double&quot; crit, x50% x2aa for up to 10k or so damage.<br>
<br>
The rarity of it would mean you couldn't Farm with it like mana burn, but we could still get the ooohhhsss and aaahhhhsss of the very very rare Uber nuke.<br>
<br>
Comments? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zuratuli>Zuratuli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 150<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/9/03 9:07 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stacking Crits?</span><hr size=1> I like this idea... It really is not overbalancing. A 1 in 500 chance to do something is rather rare. Imagine macroing a /rand 1 500 every 20 seconds for a 6 hour session. You'd /log the whole thing. Now if you parsed what you rolled... really how many 500s would you actually get? Mathematically speaking if you could maintain a nuke every 20 seconds would get atleast 2 of these out of the 1080 casts. <br>
<br>
Lets say you averaged 1,500 damage per cast (the average Icespear damage with 50% foci) you would deal 1,620,000 damage including no crits... Now if this change were to be made...  Oh no your damage output would increase 9,000 (6k for each of the 2 double critted Icespears minus the 1,500 damage that is already in the numbers).<br>
<br>
I like it... It doesn't overpower us but in some situations it may make a dramatic change for the betterment of your situation. It would also be yet another flashy thing in which would make groups want us more. <p><center><img src="http://people.ucsc.edu/~arice/pictures/zuratulisig.jpg"><br><b><font face="Comic Sans"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69194">Zuratuli</a> --  I been stompin' in my air force ones for 65 levels.</b></font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caladaar>Caladaar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/03 2:30 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stacking Crits?</span><hr size=1> Fix crits so they always do &gt;= the regular max damage of the spell.<br>
<br>
Crit'ing for single digits so powa.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tzarphkaboom>Tzarph Kaboom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/03 4:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stacking Crits?</span><hr size=1> Not all issues stem from the damage of the crit, some issues about doing less than the spells normal damage stem from damage absorption spells on the mob. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=102314"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home19.inet.tele.dk/tzarph/sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;To whack is human, to nuke is divine!&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zuratuli>Zuratuli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 155<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/03 9:22 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stacking Crits?</span><hr size=1> But critting while destroying a dmg absorb skin is not common... plus the actual damage is show in your **** has been hit by #### points of damage message anyways. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=siderius>Siderius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/12/03 4:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stacking Crits?</span><hr size=1> I have critted for less than normal spell dmg when kiting Blood Ravens in PoN. I am pretty sure he had no spell dmg absorbing things on him, since I had nuked him down to 32% hp when I critted for 132dmg with Draught of Ice that normal does 721dmg<br>
<br>
<br>
Siderius <br>
58wiz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=teilk88>Teilk88</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/14/03 10:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stacking Crits?</span><hr size=1> Critting for less than normal is because you happened to crit on a partial resist IMHO.  So the mob partials resists your Ice Comet from 1120 to 300 and then you crit on the 300 I think!<br>
<br>
Ive crit for 4 damage and 9 damage before on like 30-40ish spells!<br>
<br>
I would think it would be nice to make it so that if I crit I automatically get base damage.  I dont think that would be overpowering but would help with Damage output a little! <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=905.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=905.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=905.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=905.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=905.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=905.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub140.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName>